    "title": "Make a Plan: Student Logins",
    "long_instructions": "#### Thinking through how you want your students to access the course is an important part of planning for your first class. \r\n\r\n#### Make a plan for how you will have students log into your Code.org course. **Consider the following as you make your plan:**\r\n\r\n* #### Do my students already have Code.org accounts? \r\n* #### What type of log in will my students use? \r\n* #### How will students join my class? \r\n* #### Will I have printed instructions? Will the instructions be posted somewhere? \r\n\r\n\r\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: left; margin:20px 0px 30px 0px\">\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://forum.code.org/t/student-logins-reflection/40539\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/7dbe63a051fbad4ef262d6ab710e2966-image-1731959037460.png\" style=\"width: auto; height: 100px;\"  alt=\"A browser with two text boxes, both including an avatar and lines of text.\"></a>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #007786; border-radius: 20px 20px 20px 20px; color: #000000; width: 80%; margin-left: 5%; margin-right: 5%; padding: 10px 10px 5px 10px;\">\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><b>Post to the Code.org Forum</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.2; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\">Post your ideas and read other educators' ideas on the forum! Click on the icon to the left to direct to our forum post.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n#### Alternatively, if you prefer to reflect privately, feel free to use the text box below. Please note that once you submit, you won’t be able to view your responses again. When your students complete reflection prompts like this, you'll be able to review their responses.\r\n\r\n____\r\n\r\n#### **Note:** Click and drag the bottom-right corner of the text box below to resize it.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
